==English==
===Etymology===
From {{G.}} [[Bildung]], "[[formation]]", from [[bildunge]], from [[bildunga]], from [[bilidon]], "to shape", from [[bilodi]], "form, shape" + [[Roman]], [[novel]], from {{F.}}, [[roman]], "novel", hence "novel of education" or "novel of formation".

===Pronunciation===
*[[AHD]]: bĭldngz-rō-män′

===Noun===
'''bildungsroman''' or '''Bildungsroman'''
#Novel tracing the [[spiritual]], [[moral]], [[psychological]], or social development and growth of the main character from, [[as is often the case]], [[childhood]] to [[maturity]].

